# GitHub personal access token used only by the host workflow.
# Sandcastle strips every declared value and shadows the ignored .env file in every container.
# Create a fine-grained token: https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
# Required repository permissions:
# - Metadata: Read
# - Issues: Read and write
# - Pull requests: Read and write
# Git pushes use the repository remote credentials separately (SSH for this repository).
GH_TOKEN=
